# Project Bootstrap Init Rule

Apply this only when the current project still contains template placeholders.

## Trigger condition

If any of these exist, bootstrap is required:
- `PROJECT` in file names or file contents
- `project/project-slug` in tags
- note files named `PROJECT_*.md`

## Required behavior on first task

Before implementing the user's requested code change:
1. Detect whether placeholders still exist.
2. If they exist, ask once for:
   - project name (folder name, e.g. `NEW-APP`)
   - project tag slug (e.g. `new-app`)
3. Run bootstrap updates in the same task:
   - Replace `PROJECT` -> `<project-name>` in note links and headings.
   - Replace `project/project-slug` -> `project/<slug>`.
   - Rename files:
     - `notes/PROJECT_architecture.md` -> `notes/<project-name>_architecture.md`
     - `notes/PROJECT_requirements.md` -> `notes/<project-name>_requirements.md`
     - `notes/PROJECT_release-plan.md` -> `notes/<project-name>_release-plan.md`
4. Update `notes/_index.md` links so they match renamed files.
5. Add one entry to `CHANGELOG_DEV.md` for bootstrap initialization.

## Safety

- Do not modify application code during bootstrap.
- Only touch template/bootstrap-related docs and links.
- If placeholders are already gone, skip bootstrap and continue normal work.
